modules.description: Parses a string into a date-time tuple using a specific format, returning an error if the input is invalid. Serializes a date-time tuple into a standardized string representation. Works with Ptime's date and time components to handle calendar and clock time separately.

Provides functions to parse and generate HTTP cookies, including handling attributes like domain, path, secure, and http-only. Works with strings and custom record types representing cookie properties. Used to manage session state in web applications by encoding and decoding cookie headers.

Handles date-time parsing and serialization with precise format control, using Ptime for calendar and clock time separation. Accepts string inputs and converts them to date-time tuples, or outputs standardized strings from tuples. Supports error handling for invalid inputs and ensures consistent time representation. Can validate user-provided dates, format timestamps for logging, or convert between different time representations.
